Dialogue: 0,0:00:03.98,0:00:05.23,Titel,,0000,0000,0000,,{\c&H1010A4&}Part the First
Dialogue: 0,0:00:48.31,0:00:50.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Mr. Medicine Seller,
Dialogue: 0,0:00:52.49,0:00:55.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,we don’t want none.
Dialogue: 0,0:00:56.82,0:01:01.58,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You’ll scare off the customers, standing there like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:01.58,0:01:05.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I’ll have to ask you to leave.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:10.59,0:01:13.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No, no.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:13.59,0:01:15.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I’d like a room
Dialogue: 0,0:01:15.76,0:01:17.76,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,for the night.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:18.55,0:01:21.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes,{\alpha&HFF&} please.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:21.22,0:01:22.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, please.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:27.56,0:01:28.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh my.
Dialogue: 0,0:01:30.65,0:01:32.98,Titel,,0000,0000,0000,,{\c&H1010A4&}Long time no see
Dialogue: 0,0:01:57.43,0:02:01.76,Opening,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur2\fad(300,300)}The blue moon illuminated
Dialogue: 0,0:02:01.80,0:02:05.73,Opening,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur2\fad(300,300)}your wandering shadow.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:06.35,0:02:10.23,Opening,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur2\fad(300,300)}I could never tell you all I wanted to say.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:10.23,0:02:15.15,Opening,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur2\fad(300,250)}It was so very frustrating.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:15.23,0:02:19.03,Opening,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur2\fad(300,300)}I think about your faked smile,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:19.61,0:02:23.66,Opening,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur2\fad(300,300)}and forget all the hot tears we shed.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:24.12,0:02:26.33,Opening,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur2\fad(300,300)}What do these empty husks,
Dialogue: 0,0:02:26.37,0:02:32.17,Opening,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur2\fad(300,300)}those empty eyes of yours, reflect, my dear?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:32.92,0:02:37.38,Opening,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur2\fad(300,300)}The transient quarter moon
Dialogue: 0,0:02:37.76,0:02:39.55,Opening,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur2\fad(300,100)}hides in a rift in the clouds,
Dialogue: 1,0:02:39.51,0:02:41.93,Opening,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur2\fad(100,300)}as darkness seeps up from the ground.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:41.97,0:02:46.39,Opening,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur2\fad(300,300)}Tell me the truth, please.
Dialogue: 0,0:02:46.72,0:02:48.56,Opening,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur2\fad(300,300)}Are you so despondent
Dialogue: 0,0:02:48.64,0:02:53.02,Opening,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur2\fad(300,0)}that you still sit alone, sighing?
Dialogue: 0,0:02:53.69,0:02:55.15,Titel,,0000,0000,0000,,{\c&H1010A4&}That Night
Dialogue: 0,0:03:03.03,0:03:07.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It’s awfully cold, isn’t it?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:07.75,0:03:09.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I’m sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:11.62,0:03:13.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,But it’s bitter, isn’t it?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:14.17,0:03:16.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, it is from China.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:17.05,0:03:19.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Do you have anything else?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:21.34,0:03:24.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Do you own this inn, ma’am?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:24.68,0:03:26.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes indeed.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:26.97,0:03:31.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I’ve had the building itself since I was a girl.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:36.61,0:03:38.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What was it
Dialogue: 0,0:03:40.57,0:03:42.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,before you made it an inn?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:42.91,0:03:45.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hmm, what was it?
Dialogue: 0,0:03:45.95,0:03:47.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I forget.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:47.83,0:03:49.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Guess I’m getting old.
Dialogue: 0,0:03:54.42,0:03:55.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Excuse me!
Dialogue: 0,0:03:58.63,0:04:02.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Do you have a room for the night?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:05.47,0:04:09.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sorry, but we’re full up.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:09.52,0:04:11.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Look somewhere else.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:11.02,0:04:13.85,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You’re the only ones open!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:13.85,0:04:15.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There’re no vacancies.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.44,0:04:16.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I’ve got plenty of money!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:16.90,0:04:18.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You can even have my umbrella!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:18.32,0:04:18.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Could it be?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:18.98,0:04:20.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That’s right.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:20.44,0:04:22.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You took the last vacancy.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:21.40,0:04:22.03,Alternative,,0000,0000,0000,,Please!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:22.03,0:04:22.61,Alternative,,0000,0000,0000,,{\move(640,618,640,690,200,0)\t(50,200,\c&HE9ECF1&\3c&H262B32&)}Please!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:22.61,0:04:25.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, what about this one?
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.20,0:04:28.83,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Actually, I’m being chased.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:28.83,0:04:31.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If they find me,
Dialogue: 0,0:04:31.08,0:04:32.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I’ll be killed for sure!
Dialogue: 0,0:04:32.62,0:04:36.75,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ooh! That’s quite the story.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:41.92,0:04:43.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:44.51,0:04:46.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It’s true.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:50.14,0:04:52.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, it’s raining pretty hard.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:52.48,0:05:03.65,Alternative,,0000,0000,0000,,{\an8}We wouldn’t ordinarily turn such a\Nnice young lady as yourself away, but…
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.81,0:04:54.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It stinks.
Dialogue: 0,0:04:59.57,0:05:01.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It’s another Chinese remedy.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:01.40,0:05:05.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They call it Hansuke lotion.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.57,0:05:08.24,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You see?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:10.12,0:05:15.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If I stand in the rain any longer, my child
Dialogue: 0,0:05:17.58,0:05:19.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,will surely die!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:28.34,0:05:30.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Are you pregnant?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:32.14,0:05:37.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Goodness, I can’t believe you!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:37.73,0:05:39.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Mistress!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:39.36,0:05:43.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Tokuji, why aren’t you just kicking her out?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:44.86,0:05:49.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I’m sorry, but we don’t want any trouble.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:49.16,0:05:51.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Get out of here!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:51.03,0:05:52.70,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If I do…
Dialogue: 0,0:05:55.04,0:05:57.62,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If I do leave, by tomorrow morning
Dialogue: 0,0:06:00.96,0:06:06.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,my corpse and that of my infant\Nchild will be lying in your doorway.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:07.76,0:06:11.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don’t you think {\i1}that{\i0} would get you in a good deal of trouble?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:11.35,0:06:12.81,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I don’t take kindly to threats.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:14.10,0:06:17.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It isn’t a threat!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:17.60,0:06:21.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I want to raise a healthy child!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:21.73,0:06:24.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If I stay outside, I won’t be able to protect him!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:24.73,0:06:26.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Tokuji,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:26.07,0:06:27.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,a word.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:26.49,0:06:27.15,Alternative,,0000,0000,0000,,Please!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.15,0:06:28.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Sure.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:28.36,0:06:29.78,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Please!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:29.78,0:06:32.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Please! Please!
Dialogue: 0,0:06:30.16,0:06:32.41,Alternative,,0000,0000,0000,,Take her upstairs.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:32.41,0:06:34.16,Alternative,,0000,0000,0000,,{\move(640,618,640,690,200,0)\t(50,200,\c&HE9ECF1&\3c&H262B32&)}Take her upstairs.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:34.16,0:06:35.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wha—!?{Whaaa?}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:35.16,0:06:37.16,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\i1}That{\i0} room?
Dialogue: 0,0:06:43.92,0:06:46.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It can’t be helped.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:47.72,0:06:52.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I’ll take her there, you get a bed ready.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:53.89,0:06:54.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:06:55.89,0:06:58.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Um, I…
Dialogue: 0,0:07:00.60,0:07:02.94,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I am in your debt.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:15.70,0:07:16.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There we go.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:21.67,0:07:25.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,She could have stayed in my room.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:36.31,0:07:41.48,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,We don’t usually let customers in\Nthis room, so keep this to yourself.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:41.48,0:07:44.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Just try not to cause any trouble.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:44.40,0:07:45.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I will.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:48.44,0:07:50.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Um, ma’am?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:50.90,0:07:52.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What now?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:52.74,0:07:56.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I don’t care what it is, but I’d like something to eat.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:04.08,0:08:07.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I wonder who did this.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:07.25,0:08:11.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, I’ll have Tokuji take care of it in the morning.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:13.34,0:08:16.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I couldn’t make much more than a bit of rice.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:16.14,0:08:17.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That’s just fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:38.45,0:08:40.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What are you doing?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:42.50,0:08:46.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They’re up awfully late.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:46.17,0:08:51.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You’ll be able to eat all you like, soon.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:51.92,0:08:54.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You really want this child, don’t you?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:54.59,0:08:55.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I do.
Dialogue: 0,0:08:55.68,0:09:00.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I’m obviously not privy to all the\Ndetails, but can you really raise it on your own?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:00.97,0:09:02.18,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I intend to.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:02.18,0:09:03.98,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ah, do you now?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:03.98,0:09:08.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well, at least you’re young.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:08.31,0:09:10.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Seems a bit naive, though.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:10.23,0:09:14.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You don’t even have a steady supply of food.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:14.57,0:09:18.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Are you sure you’re not giving birth simply out of spite?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:19.20,0:09:22.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Do you think it would be happy with no-one to care for it?
Dialogue: 0,0:09:29.79,0:09:31.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I…
Dialogue: 0,0:09:34.09,0:09:37.05,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I want him to live.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:40.22,0:09:45.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What a strange woman. So strong-willed, almost to a fault.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:48.73,0:09:54.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I was never able to do anything as irresponsible as that.
Dialogue: 0,0:09:50.69,0:09:52.69,Alternative,,0000,0000,0000,,Ma’am?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:12.38,0:10:14.80,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So warm.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:14.80,0:10:17.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Your bed will be here shortly.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:17.26,0:10:18.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, right.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:18.97,0:10:21.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I have to make you some food, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:27.27,0:10:31.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you so much.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:44.91,0:10:46.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A doll?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:53.67,0:10:56.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey there, Medicine Seller, what’s the matter?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:57.51,0:11:01.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I was heading to the lavatory.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:01.55,0:11:03.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I got a little lost.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:03.43,0:11:05.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, well then.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:05.14,0:11:07.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It’s just at the end of that hall.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:13.11,0:11:14.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:19.03,0:11:21.15,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Are there any rooms above here?
Dialogue: 0,0:11:21.15,0:11:25.37,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,None at all. It’s just a storeroom.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:25.37,0:11:27.12,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I would ask you not to go up.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:31.08,0:11:32.96,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:32.96,0:11:35.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh, I should pay for those medicines.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:36.80,0:11:39.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No,
Dialogue: 0,0:11:39.17,0:11:41.47,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,tomorrow will be fine.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:44.68,0:11:46.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Good night to you.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:52.02,0:11:56.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Where did I drop my charm?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:00.32,0:12:01.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Give that back!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:12.21,0:12:13.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Where did you…
Dialogue: 0,0:12:13.71,0:12:14.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Give it back!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:15.88,0:12:17.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(0,200)}Give it back!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:17.92,0:12:20.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,{\fad(0,200)}Give it back!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:20.17,0:12:21.55,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Give it back!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:25.30,0:12:26.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Is it yours?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:27.35,0:12:28.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yup.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:32.31,0:12:34.14,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I’m so sorry.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:34.14,0:12:36.40,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Here you are.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:38.32,0:12:39.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Are you pregnant?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:40.07,0:12:42.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I am.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:42.65,0:12:47.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It shouldn’t be more than four months or so now.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:47.82,0:12:49.33,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Are you happy?
Dialogue: 0,0:12:49.33,0:12:51.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Yes, of course.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:51.41,0:12:53.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Hey, let’s go over there.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:53.87,0:12:55.25,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I’m afraid not.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:55.25,0:12:58.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You should get back to your own roo—
Dialogue: 0,0:13:14.14,0:13:15.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,So cold.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:54.85,0:13:57.31,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I will {\i1}not{\i0} return home!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:57.31,0:13:59.06,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Leave me be!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:59.06,0:14:03.07,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Do not give birth to this child.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:03.07,0:14:06.53,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If it were to come back and claim its birthright,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:06.53,0:14:10.91,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,it would be quite an inconvenience to the master and mistress.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:10.91,0:14:13.79,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I’ve cut myself off from the young master!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:13.79,0:14:19.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That ignorant little fool does not concern me.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:20.92,0:14:23.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I just want to give birth!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:25.42,0:14:27.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That’s all!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:39.35,0:14:42.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I can’t return empty-handed, having come all this way.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:42.52,0:14:43.82,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don’t kill me!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:44.57,0:14:46.99,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No! Please!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:46.99,0:14:47.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My son!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:47.90,0:14:48.36,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Ready to die?
Dialogue: 0,0:14:49.03,0:14:49.86,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,My son!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:49.86,0:14:50.49,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Prepare to die.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:50.49,0:14:53.03,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Think of my son!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:47.05,0:15:48.26,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:07.19,0:16:10.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Just what is going on here?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:11.70,0:16:14.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What is this?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:12.61,0:16:14.41,Alternative,,0000,0000,0000,,What are you doing here?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:14.41,0:16:15.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Did you do this?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:17.74,0:16:19.04,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Of course not.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:19.45,0:16:23.67,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh no! It’s all because you let her stay in this room!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:19.45,0:16:21.29,Alternative,,0000,0000,0000,,It protected her?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:21.29,0:16:23.67,Alternative,,0000,0000,0000,,But why?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:23.67,0:16:24.42,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Tokuji!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:24.42,0:16:27.59,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Go run to the castle.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:27.59,0:16:31.17,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That will not be necessary.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:31.17,0:16:33.30,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Of course it’s necessary!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:33.30,0:16:35.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Only a criminal would object to calling the authorities!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:35.64,0:16:37.60,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You must have done it!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:36.14,0:16:37.60,Alternative,,0000,0000,0000,,He didn’t!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:38.26,0:16:40.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I saw it.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:40.68,0:16:43.64,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He was not the culprit.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:45.44,0:16:46.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:47.98,0:16:49.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What, then,
Dialogue: 0,0:16:50.69,0:16:52.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,did you see?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:56.45,0:16:59.45,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,He was caught, and pulled up.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:59.45,0:17:01.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Then spun around.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:01.66,0:17:04.50,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Around and around and around and around.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:04.50,0:17:07.38,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Oh?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:07.38,0:17:10.88,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Around and around and around and around?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:13.13,0:17:14.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Medicine Seller?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:14.93,0:17:17.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Just who are you?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:17.68,0:17:20.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What are you doing in this room, anyway?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:21.22,0:17:26.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The culprit was not human.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:29.23,0:17:30.61,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It opened by itself.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:33.74,0:17:35.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What is that?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:36.66,0:17:42.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Wh—Why would a medicine seller\Nbe carrying such a ridiculous sword?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:42.08,0:17:45.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,I came to kill.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:47.29,0:17:49.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,K—Kill what?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:56.38,0:17:59.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The Mononoke, of course.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:00.39,0:18:02.97,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Something must have killed him.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:03.47,0:18:06.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Don’t be stupid!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:06.43,0:18:08.35,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,As you can see, though,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:08.35,0:18:10.11,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,he was indeed killed.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:10.11,0:18:11.65,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Could any man do this?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:11.65,0:18:12.90,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Well of course—
Dialogue: 0,0:18:12.90,0:18:13.44,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Not.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:14.15,0:18:15.74,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There, there.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:16.95,0:18:18.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What a terrible smell.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:18.20,0:18:20.87,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What is that doing here?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:22.66,0:18:24.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Where did it come from?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:24.29,0:18:26.20,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It was here from the beginning.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:26.79,0:18:28.08,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A child came to get it.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:28.08,0:18:29.29,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,A child?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:29.29,0:18:31.13,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There must be some here.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:31.13,0:18:33.09,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What are you talking about?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:33.09,0:18:36.72,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,None of tonight’s customers had children with them.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:36.72,0:18:40.68,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Th—Then, what were those footsteps, and children’s voices?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:41.22,0:18:44.22,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,You must have heard them when we were walking up here.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:44.22,0:18:45.39,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,No, I didn’t.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:45.39,0:18:46.93,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:48.98,0:18:49.89,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:49.89,0:18:52.77,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There’s a group of children right over there!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:59.36,0:19:01.32,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What now?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:02.87,0:19:05.66,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Over there, too!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:10.79,0:19:11.54,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:19:15.05,0:19:16.21,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And above us!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:16.21,0:19:19.51,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,What do you mean? This is the top floor!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:19.51,0:19:20.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The body…
Dialogue: 0,0:19:21.18,0:19:22.01,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,It’s gone.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:23.43,0:19:25.43,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,They’re coming from right over there!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:27.02,0:19:28.10,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And from there!
Dialogue: 0,0:19:34.48,0:19:36.19,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,That’s as far as you’ll come!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:05.22,0:20:10.02,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,There are Mononoke here that are bound to this inn.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:10.02,0:20:13.73,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Children, babies’ cries, and
Dialogue: 0,0:20:14.98,0:20:16.52,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,birth water?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:16.52,0:20:19.23,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,This is a Zashikiwarashi.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:21.11,0:20:24.57,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Certain conditions must be met for\Nthe Sword of Exorcism to be drawn.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:24.57,0:20:29.41,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,If Form, Truth, and Regret are\Nnot present, it cannot be unsheathed.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:30.29,0:20:33.92,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,The intertwined fates of men give the Mononoke its Form,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:33.92,0:20:36.71,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,Truth is the natural state of all things,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:36.71,0:20:40.46,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,and Regret is ever-present in men’s hearts.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:40.46,0:20:42.84,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,And so, I’ll ask you all
Dialogue: 0,0:20:50.10,0:20:52.27,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,to tell me
Dialogue: 0,0:20:53.69,0:20:56.69,Default,,0000,0000,0000,,the Truth and Regret!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:07.53,0:21:09.95,Titel,,0000,0000,0000,,{\pos(640,715)\c&H1010A4&}To be continued
Dialogue: 0,0:21:11.75,0:21:19.25,Ending,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur1\fad(300,300)}Without you, I just can’t smile.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:20.38,0:21:30.31,Ending,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur1\fad(300,300)}I walk this banal town,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:30.31,0:21:36.39,Ending,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur1\fad(300,300)}feeling such intense emotions.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:36.94,0:21:42.78,Ending,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur1\fad(300,300)}I know that if I could treasure them and live on,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:42.86,0:21:52.08,Ending,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur1\fad(300,300)}I would need nothing else.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:52.74,0:22:00.25,Ending,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur1\fad(300,300)}The summer flowers that bloomed in the sky
Dialogue: 0,0:22:00.25,0:22:06.55,Ending,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur1\fad(300,300)}Come falling down, dancing in the wind.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:06.63,0:22:09.89,Ending,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur1\fad(300,300)}I can barely recall the night sky
Dialogue: 0,0:22:09.89,0:22:13.18,Ending,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur1\fad(300,300)}where they all came tumbling down,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:13.18,0:22:24.03,Ending,,0000,0000,0000,,{\blur1\fad(300,300)}so what I can still recall is all the more precious.
